INTRODUCTION: Life expectancy is important to inform a number of clinical 
decisions in primary care but its communication is challenging for clinicians.
METHODS: This qualitative interview study with 40 community-dwelling older 
adults explored their perspectives on how and when to discuss life expectancy in 
primary care.
